= "Agrarian Bolshevism"

One of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP":<span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP":<span style="color: #000000;">CVP</span>?]'s Labor Minister Adam Stegerwald’s pet projects is the dismantling of hopelessly bankrupt eastern estates to carve them into peasant homesteads. The problem is that there haven’t been many young workers eager to turn themselves into peasants.

Still, with <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">**CNBLP**</span> member Hans Schlange-Schöningen newly sworn in as Commissar for Eastern Aid—following Treviranus’s move to the Transport Ministry—he’s struck a deal with Stegerwald: estates deemed “hopelessly bankrupt” will be handed over to the Labor Ministry. Backed by his promise to the unions, Stegerwald has pushed a decree that allows the government to purchase select estates at prices set by the Eastern Aid office.

Unfortunately for Brüning, a copy of the decree has been leaked to the National Rural League (RLB). Its lobbyists—deeply embedded in Hindenburg’s circle—have denounced it as "<span style="color: #385A38;">Agrarian</span> <span style="color: #9B0000;">Bolshevism</span>" slamming the measure as a descent into <span style="color: #9B0000;">state socialism</span>. They’ve made sure the President, who along with many friends owns eastern estates, see it as a personal attack.

- @joever

